In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer discussed President Trump's legislative priorities, including tax reform and the repeal and replacement of Obamacare. Spicer highlighted the need for significant tax reform to simplify the tax code and create jobs. He also emphasized the urgency to repeal and replace Obamacare, citing the failures of the healthcare law. Spicer also provided updates on Tech Week, which focuses on advancing technological innovation and economic growth. He mentioned the President's visit to Cedar Rapids, Iowa to witness technological advancements in agriculture, as well as the demonstrations of drones and universal broadband at the White House. Spicer also addressed questions about the death of Otto Warmbier and the U.S. relationship with China, as well as the ongoing healthcare debate and the President's support for the coal industry.